12 2.1 Functional Split
PC P P P C FD1: 1T1R, 1CC, 100MHz, 30KHz SCS
FD2: 4T4R, 1CC, 100MHz, 30KHz SCS
FD3: 8T8R, 2CC, 20 MHz 40 MHz, 100MHz, 2CC same BW per carrier, 30KHz SCS (4 users with 2 stream each, 2 users with 4 stream each, or 8 users with single stream each), 2 static beam 4T4R. Support for DPD.
FD4: 8T8R, 2CC, Any BW, 2CC same BW per carrier,, 4 static beam 2T2R. Support for DPD, 15KHz SCS

45 3.1.3.1.6 ecpriRtcid / ecpriPcid (real time control data / IQ data transfer message series identifier)
PC P P P C Only endpoints that support a single numerology are supported. Sequence checkers are not implemented, and each message is dealt with relying only on its transported symbol number. Sub field selection can be handled by means of shift and mask variables. Within the RU_Port_ID assignment, a rule must be defined to distinguish packets carrying PxxCH traffic, from those transporting either SSB or PRACH content. FD1, FD2, FD3: Fixed values for eCPRIRtcid/eCPRIPcid are supported from different profiles.
FD4: Support for both Static and Variable configuration can be done through M-Plane.
46 3.1.3.1.7 ecpriSeqid (message identifier)
PC P P P P FD1 to FD4 - application layer fragmentation is supported, therefore the Sequence ID field is regularly incremented per eAxC after any generated packet.

84 5.3.2 Mixed Numerology and PRACH Handling
PC P P P C In case Section Type 3, messages are used, the Frequency Offset associated to each section, as well as the Time Offset and other relevant information associated to the header are extracted. In case of PRACH both the frameStructure and the frequencyOffset associated to each section in a Section Type 3 are extracted, thus allowing to manage different Frequency Blocks. Same as release mapping in 2.1

PRACH:
FD1, FD2, FD3: Short Preamble Format B4
FD4: Support for both Short Preamble Format B4, C2 and Long Preamble Format 0, Configuration can be done through M-Plane.

Each CC can be assigned its own numerology and number of sub-carriers grouped in RBs.

Shall support One Type 3 message for all repeated PRACH preambles.

Shall support Type 3 message per repeated PRACH preambles

O-RU expects timeOffset without CP_Length.
